  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2017-06-20T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Congressional Personal Safety Act\n\nThis bill amends the federal criminal code to allow a Member of Congress who is carrying a valid Member identification document and who is not otherwise prohibited from transporting, shipping, or receiving a firearm to carry a firearm for any lawful purpose: (1) in any state; and (2) in the Capitol Buildings, other than the U.S. Capitol, and on the Capitol Grounds."
  }, 
